					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Use a sprite with the new color on top of the first letter of each pair, and when the second letter changes you get rid of the sprite and modify the attributes, coloring both letters.
<br />
<br />The downside is that you are gonna need all the letters in both sides of the pattern table (unless you use 8x16 sprites, but then you'd need an empty tile for each letter, which would waste just as many tiles). So yeah, the downside is that you're gonna be wasting some tiles.</div>

